# Experimental 64k-context variant of ministral-3:8b for Open Code on M1 16GB.
#
# Why: Ollama docs recommend at least 64k tokens for agentic tools like Open Code.
# 16k can run out during multi-file sessions where context accumulates across
# tool calls, file reads, and conversation history.
#
# Memory warning: at 64k the KV cache grows significantly alongside the ~6GB
# model weights. On M1 16GB this may cause partial CPU offload. Test before
# committing to this variant:
#
#   ollama create ministral-3:8b-64k -f modelfiles/ministral-3-8b-64k.Modelfile
#   ollama run ministral-3:8b-64k
#   # In a second terminal:
#   ollama ps
#   # Look for "100% GPU" — anything less means CPU spillover and slower inference.
#
# Build:  ollama create ministral-3:8b-64k -f modelfiles/ministral-3-8b-64k.Modelfile

FROM ministral-3:8b
PARAMETER num_ctx 65536
